names.details: Nehr-i İs̱īl: It is as big as the Tigris. It flows from the lands of Rūm and Bulgar to the lands of the Khazars. According to the scholars, it eventually pours again into the Khazar Sea. Particularly, seventy-five rivers branch off from it, yet it neither decreases nor changes. Even after it joins the sea, it continues to flow for a distance of two days clearly; it does not change its color. It doesn't change its appearance. In the sea, it can be easily distinguished. Moreover, in the winter season, it freezes. It includes peculiar types of aquatic animals. (Translated from Ottoman Turkish to English by the first creator of the name.)
